\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. tridentatum} (L.) P. Gibbs,{\i   Feddes Repert.}{\b  79}: 54 (1968) ({\i  Genistella tridentata} (L.) Samp.,{\i   Pterospartum tridentatum} (L.) Willk.; incl.{\i   P. cantabricum} (Spach) Willk.{\i   P. lasianthum} (Spach) Willk., {\i  P. stenopterum }(Spach) Willk. Erect or procumbent, much-branched shrub 30-70 cm; wings undulate, rather coriaceous, contracted at each node to form 3 teeth or lobes. Leaves absent. Calyx 4-7 mm, sericeous; corolla 8-12 mm, the standard glabrous to densely sericeous. Legume 10-12 × c. 4 mm, pubescent. Seeds strophiolate.{\i   Heaths and scrub on acid soils.  • W. part of the Iberian peninsula.} Hs Lu.
