\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. E. horridum} (Vahl) Rothm., {\i  Bot. Jahrb.}{\b  72}: 80 (1941) ({\i  Genista horrida} (Vahl) DC.). Up to 40 cm, spiny. Leaves 4-9 mm, narrowly oblanceolate, sericeous beneath, glabrescent above; pulvini prominent. Flowers usually 2 on each branch, opposite. Calyx 7-12 mm, sparsely sericeous; teeth acute. Standard 12-16 mm, glabrescent to sparsely sericeous. Legume 9-14 × 4-4·5 mm 2n = 44.{\i   Exposed mountain rocks and slopes; calcicole. •  Pyrenees and S.C. France.} Ga Hs.
